The paper deals with the problem of deriving a specification for a third-party component, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the theory of input-output conformance (ioco) testing, which is a formal method used to test software components (cs.PL). The concept of decompositionality, which is a key focus of the paper, is related to the logical organization of software components (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the criteria for strong decomposability, which is a property of software components that ensures their correctness when composed with other components (cs.FL). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of conformance testing, which is a topic in the field of embedded systems (cs.ET).
